<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-444-157  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 444 157.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 21 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for Mac: Writenow v2.2 ships in the UK. (Apple Macintosh wordprocessing package)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Persona-TMC (product enhancement).andO;Product:   WriteNow 2.2 (Word processing software) (product enhancement).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersEnhancementsWord processing softwareEngland.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR MAC: Writenow v2.2 Ships In The UK CHESSINGTON, SURREY, ENGLAND, 1990AUG 21 (NB) -- Persona-TMC has announced the shipment of the English versionof Writenow v2.2, the word processing package for the Apple Mac, in the UK.andO;The software, which retails for UKP 170, comes with a UK dictionary andthesaurus.andM;&quot;Unlike the majority of word processing programs in the US, Writenow v.2.2overcomes the usual spelling check problems by incorporating a 116,000 wordUK dictionary and thesaurus,&quot; said Tim Felmingham, Persona-TMC's director.andM;The dictionary used in the new version of Writenow is a disk- based versionof the Williams-Collins dictionary.andP;  The thesaurus, meanwhile, is supplied byProximity/Collins.andM;The new word processing package includes over 24 new features andimprovements, the company claims.andP;  The features list now includes a newfont/size and  format accelerator, optional menu fonts, ruler guides for fastvisual alignment and date formatting.andM;Existing users of Writenow can upgrade from version 1.0 to v2.2 for UKP 70,while version 2.0 users can upgrade for UKP 45.andP;  Existing users of anyversion can obtain a copy of the dictionary upgrade free of charge.andM;(Steve Gold/19900813/Press andamp; Public Contact: Persona-TMC - Tel: 0372-729611)</TEXT></DOC>